 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z\"></path></svg></a>What is Day2Day?</h2>\n<p>Day2Day is a task manager I wrote soperating on Google Docs.<br>\nItâ€™s simple and it just works. ğŸ˜ƒ<br>\nI have tried a lot of productivity apps, some are great but too overwhelming. Lots of features that I donâ€™t need, it becomes hard to do simple things.</p>\n<h2 id=\"why-would-i-use-day2day\"><a href=\"#why-would-i-use-day2day\" aria-hidden class=\"anchor\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" height=\"16\" version=\"1.1\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\" width=\"16\"><path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z\"></path></svg></a>Why would I use Day2Day?</h2>\n<p>Well, letâ€™s see what people think about it:</p>\n<p><em>â€œAll of a sudden, I was able to leave my office by 3pm!â€</em> â€” Marta<br>\n<em>â€œI didnâ€™t want to believe it, but Day2Day brought order to my life!â€</em> â€” Pierre<br>\n<em>â€œMy productivity increased by +200% after using Day2Day for only 1 day! ğŸ¤¯â€</em> â€” Pavel  </p>\n<h2 id=\"how-does-day2day-work\"><a href=\"#how-does-day2day-work\" aria-hidden class=\"anchor\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" height=\"16\" version=\"1.1\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\" width=\"16\"><path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z\"></path></svg></a>How does Day2Day work?</h2>\n<p>Every day, you will write your tasks and subtasks on a Google Docs, following the pre-filled template provided by my script.<br>\nIn order to mark the task as done, you only have to strikethrough it. (Cmd+shift+x on Mac or Alt+Shift+5 on Windows/Linux)<br>\nThe script will be run automatically every weekday at midnight, will copy the uncompleted tasks from the previous day and paste it to the new day.<br>\nNo need for any manual work here. ğŸ¥³</p>\n<h2 id=\"motivation--previous-work\"><a href=\"#motivation--previous-work\" aria-hidden class=\"anchor\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" height=\"16\" version=\"1.1\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\" width=\"16\"><path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z\"></path></svg></a>Motivation &#x26; Previous work</h2>\n<p>I am using this Google Docs for daily tasks for a few years now. I always found it too much to copy-paste the previous day, to remove the completed tasks, every single day. (Yes, I like automation! ğŸ¤–)  </p>\n<p>So I wrote a React Web App to do this job for me, the code is available here. But after a while, it became too complex for the simple task manager I needed, so I wrote Day2Day on Google App Script. (ie, the content of this article)  </p>\n<p>You can see a quick demo of my previous work:</p>\n<p><img src=\"/bbc5293be5d966aba46091117755c880/day2day_gif.gif\" alt=\"First version Day2Day\"></p>\n<p>It would also generate what you have to say for your team <strong>Standup</strong>. ğŸ˜…</p>\n<p>There is also a Markdown editor useful to simply store important information, that you might want to quickly find for instance when itâ€™s time for Promo season in your company.</p>\n<h2 id=\"how-to-set-day2day-up\"><a href=\"#how-to-set-day2day-up\" aria-hidden class=\"anchor\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" height=\"16\" version=\"1.1\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\" width=\"16\"><path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z\"></path></svg></a>How to set Day2Day up?</h2>\n<p>You can follow these 8 simple steps:<br>\nI donâ€™t want this article to be too long here, so please go to <a href=\"https://medium.com/@papay0/day2day-task-manager-operating-on-google-docs-bca099d75e45\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow noopener noreferrer\">my original medium article</a> and the 8 easy steps are explained. ğŸ˜ˆ</p>\n<p>You can now start writing your tasks following the same pattern as the picture on the top of this article, ie using bulleted lists.</p>\n<p>Enjoy! ğŸ¥³</p>\n<h2 id=\"how-to-contribute-ğŸ¤©\"><a href=\"#how-to-contribute-%F0%9F%A4%A9\" aria-hidden class=\"anchor\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" height=\"16\" version=\"1.1\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\" width=\"16\"><path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z\"></path></svg></a>How to contribute ğŸ¤©</h2>\n<p>Day2Day is open sourced!<br>\nSimply go to the <a href=\"https://github.com/papay0/Day2Day\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow noopener noreferrer\">GitHub project</a> and go for it, Iâ€™m waiting for your PR ğŸ˜ƒ</p>","timeToRead":2,"frontmatter":{"title":"Day2Day, your task manager operating on Google Docs ğŸ¤“","date":"February 04, 2020","spoiler":"Trust me you will feel so good after using it for two days!","category":"project"},"fields":{"slug":"/day2day/","langKey":"en"}}},"pageContext":{"slug":"/day2day/","previous":{"fields":{"slug":"/f8-2019/","langKey":"en","directoryName":"f8-2019"},"frontmatter":{"title":"My Facebook F8/Hackathons 2019 Experience ğŸ˜"}},"next":{"fields":{"slug":"/lifegorithms-goal/","langKey":"en","directoryName":"lifegorithms-goal"},"frontmatter":{"title":"Lifegorithms, what is it about? ğŸ¤”"}},"translations":[],"translatedLinks":[]}}}